cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.HC 

This paper deals with image recognition using deep neural networks and compares their performance with that of humans under visual distortions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the internal representation of images in DNNs and the human visual system, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The comparison of performance between DNNs and humans also involves aspects of machine learning, which could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the potential for future development of more robust DNNs, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the comparison of performance between DNNs and humans involves aspects of human-computer interaction, which could be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
